James Bond star actress, Olga Kurylenko has been tested positive for the novel coronavirus. The talented actress, who is best known for the James Bond 007 movie where she played Bond girl Camille Montes and sci-fi film Oblivion confirmed this in a post on her Instagram page. The 40-year-old actress warned her fans to take the deadly virus serious and stay safe. “Locked up at home after having tested positive for Coronavirus. “I’ve actually been ill for almost a week now. Fever and fatigue are the main symptoms. “Take care of yourself and do take this seriously!” Kurylenko who has dual French-Russian citizenship starred in Oblivion, Hitman, Quantum of Solace amongst other blockbuster movies. DAILY POST recalls that Oscar-winning actor Tom Hanks confirmed last week that he and his wife, actress and singer Rita Wilson, tested positive for the virus as well.